Vince,<br>
<br>
I just noticed your post. How convenient for you to talk about cockblocking sitting in the elemental planes, when you had how many chances at Rallos before he went on Rotation? Now guilds that get to the point of trying him are going to get their one shot per rotation? Please, get on one side or the other of the discussion. I accept he's on rotation and NB is going to take a lot longer to get our attempts in against him than Tindi or BOTS did, but for you to sit there and paint guilds that don't like teaming as &quot;cockblockers&quot; and while sitting on the other side of the Rallos Zek rotation is a bit much. <br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
I do not know the history here, though my imagination does wander; <br>
<br>
It has always been, detrimental or not, the case that the first guild to kill a mob gets it pretty much unfettered; the second guild to kill the same mob, may or may not work out a rotation with the first; but there are always a few that get to kill it often compared to the guilds entering into a rotation. <br>
<br>
The situation with Ralloz Zek and who is on the rotation notwithstanding; depending on the circumstances, it may well be hypocritical to take a position on 'cockblocking' when a guild makes it onto a rotation before another, but lets remember the distinction here; there is no rotation on Aerin Dar. <br>
<br>
Had there been one, justified in some way, this would not have happened. <br>
<br>
And for the record, I don't think people that don't like teaming are cockblockers by definition; I think there are many, like you Karadin, that feel it is 'cheating' our system and I respect the urge to change that. <br>
<br>
However, I do not feel that extending current conventions is the answer, nor do I think it is an appropriate situation to extend conventions to; if we want to discuss new approaches, I think that is just fine, and will obviously willingly discuss a solution that is fair to all.<br>
<br>
Yers,<br>
