</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#222222><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/btherathetravelagency.showUserPublicProfile?gid=gradukk>Gradukk</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/misc_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Tindi Losi - GL</span><br>  Posts: 66<br> <font color=#00FFFF>(4/2/03 6:18:04 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm11.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=297.topic&index=22>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://monkey.thirty4.com/images/eq/tindi/975.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Teaming</span><hr size=1> Here is the problem as I see it. Maybe this will be stated in a way that makes more sense. Currently there are many many mobs that are 'not on rotation' that do allow access to other zones that people can 'xp' in.<br>
<br>
These mobs include Terris Thule, Behemoth, Grummus, and of course Aerin`Dar. After this point, there becomes other mobs that stand in the way of accessing Sol Ro Tower, which is a zone that can support MASSIVE amounts of 'xp' groups if they wanted to do it. These mobs include Mith Marr, Saryrn, Bertoxx, Tallon and Vallon Zek.<br>
<br>
Now, lets say a guild can get into HoH, Tactics, CoD, and Torment by themselves. Then smaller guilds decide to team up, or even run FFA flagging raids, where they just invite tons of small guild or non guilded people, and zerg the encounters to death, then these people pour into CoD, HoH, Tactics, etc..<br>
<br>
Now you have these zones swamped with people that took the short and fast way into a new xp zone, only to discover it is now overcrowded and not worth being in for anyone, JUST LIKE PoN! Heheh. So now the guilds that got into these zones say WTF?!? this place sucks now, we need new xp grounds, LoM and VoF (just making this up) decide they want to get into Sol Ro Tower to escape the mass throng of people. So they team up to take down Mith Marr, Bertoxx, Saryrn, and the Zek twins..Now they are in Sol Ro Tower.<br>
<br>
So what, right? Well this leads to even more problems. Now it takes even longer for solo guilds to get to the top, due to people double teaming the mobs the solo guilds HAVE TO KILL to get flagged up to where they are trying to get to. The teaming guilds are taking content away from the guilds that have to kill these mobs to get where they need to be. This is what none of the guilds past tier 2 want to see.<br>
<br>
Now I understand, you may not want anything more than instant access to HoH rather than doing the timesink quest. However, others could use the same precident, to basically clear all the way up the chain to the stopper which would be Rallos (since it is on rotation). You could even possibly have a 2 team guild that decides to merge all other rotations for a month, take down Rallos a few times, then 'break' the alliance, and within a week be back on all their old rotations separately. Meanwhile sitting pretty in the Elemental Planes, where there is lots of room to xp, minibosses that they COULD kill as a seperate guilds that drop elemental armor, and reap the massive bonuses of all the elemental tradeskill loots that can be farmed by single groups.<br>
<br>
Meanwhile, guilds that choose to go solo get left behind while guilds that have chosen to ally up to the top, get all the benefits of doing so, to the detriment of the other guilds that had to go it alone. I'm sure both BotS and Tindi and eventually NB and others, would not want to share the elemental armor drops (which are not too common when the goal is to equip your entire guild just to defeat the elemental gods to get into PoTime) with guilds that have no intentions of leaving the elemental planes for a long long time, and just want to rake in loot they cannot put to use due to the difficulty of the Elemental gods...<br>
<br>
Teaming on these tier 1-2 bosses will set precidence if not looked at soon, and we will end up seeing an allied Bertox kill which will open up another can of worms entirely, since he is the biggest stopper on the way to Sol Ro Tower.<br>
<br>
That is the fear of any of these guilds that have moved into the tier 3-4 zones alone. I personally could care less if AD dies to anyone, because I am in the Elemental planes, however I'm sure VoF, LoM, SoTE and others sitting where they are, would and may feel differently about that.<br>
<br>
What is the solution? I don't know at this point. AD on rotation is absurd. But how else do you enforce anything without it being part of the rotation system.<br>
<br>
Now on CB and VoLS side of the fence. I have been there before. Teaming up to get to a less crowded(for now) xp area makes so much sense, as opposed to it taking 100 times as long by doing the single questing system. Grats on the kill even, AD is a difficult mob, and takes skill and sometimes a bit of luck. NB is not concerned about you guys having access to 'xp', but if you all decided later to advance beyond, there is nothing to stop you from teaming all the way up the flag chain, or others from doing it and then using you all as an example of why it is ok for them to do it.<br>
<br>
Some think that this is fine, some do not, it definately deserves to be looked into further, and an agreement needs to be made on how teaming flag mobs is handled other than just the no piggy backing clause.<br>
<br>
Discuss. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/btherathetravelagency.showUserPublicProfile?gid=kelonybc>KelonYBC</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Shadows of Yamabushi</span><br>  Posts: 46<br> <font color=#00FFFF>(4/2/03 10:28:41 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm11.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=297.topic&index=23>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Teaming</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>The teaming guilds are taking content away from the guilds that have to kill these mobs to get where they need to be. This is what none of the guilds past tier 2 want to see.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
And this, I think, is truly the heart of the problem.  If you are there already, you try to protect your turf and reap the rewards from them as uncontested as possible for as long as possible.  Now, this does not mean that you actively block other guilds by perma-killing flag mobs, but it does mean that you try to enforce rules on non-rotational mobs that state that &quot;if you don't do it like we did, you can't do it&quot;.  <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>I'm sure both BotS and Tindi and eventually NB and others, would not want to share the elemental armor drops (which are not too common when the goal is to equip your entire guild just to defeat the elemental gods to get into PoTime) with guilds that have no intentions of leaving the elemental planes for a long long time, and just want to rake in loot they cannot put to use due to the difficulty of the Elemental gods...<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
Same sentiment.  You are sitting there pretty uncontested, farm to your hearts' delight and, in a perfect world, don't want to share if it was up to you.  Although I do not understand fully why guilds that would get to the elemental planes would not benefit from those drops there.<br>
<br>
I think there really is not much to say to the whole thing.  It is clear that guilds that made it to tier 3/4 would like the status quo of personal farming grounds in these zones to stay the way it is, while guilds trying to advance to the next tiers to improve their guild (which in turn allows them to do more difficult mobs) see any restrictions imposed by tier 3/4 guilds as simple attempts to keep them away as long as possible.  I don't see how you can find a solution that everybody is happy with, so the question becomes whose interests you are going to put first. <p><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><br>
