</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#222222><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/btherathetravelagency.showUserPublicProfile?gid=ameliarespiritblade>Ameliare Spiritblade</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Sancrosanct Legion - GL</span><br>  Posts: 119<br> <font color=#00FFFF>(4/2/03 9:19:46 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm11.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=297.topic&index=26>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Teaming</span><hr size=1> I can understand, while not agree with, the desire of those already past Aerin dar to prefer to keep the playground to themselves.  Seeing as how there are ways to quest the flag, as opposed to killing the mob for it, I don't truly see how making a no-teaming rule for this will really do any good.  I can understand a no-teaming rule for things that are non-questable, but I disagree with the fairness of it.<br>
<br>
It's all relative to the sandbox theory.  You take a child, put them in a sandbox and watch them.  Another child is welcome as they want company.  However, when the children start to flock towards the sandbox because of the cool toys, watch those already *in* the sandbox get angry and refuse to let them in.  They want to keep it to themselves.<br>
<br>
Whereas we're not children, the theory still holds water.<br>
<br>
I admit I don't have a ready answer on how to make future encounters less painful, but I'm open to suggestions until I come up with something.  :&quot;)<br>
