<br>
<br>
I wasn't going to reply (because of people complaining about the thoroughness of my posts), but since people seem to think you've &quot;stumped&quot; the guilds who object to teaming, I have to.<br>
<br>
The reason your recommendation won't work is twofold.<br>
<br>
1)  It sets a precedent that PoP mobs can be teamed up on, while guilds remain separate for all other rotations.  This is against the basic convention established when Trak rotation was first set up - kill the mob on your own to get on rotation.  This precedent will be used later, maybe not by you, as reason why all PoP mobs can be teamed on.  If no teaming is allowed, it's consistent.<br>
2)  What is then to stop an Alliance from forming just until Rallos is dead, then breaks up.  If you want to do that now, by all means, but you will have had to work through all PoP content as a single alliance for all rotations, and will have paid the same price the rest of us do.  And if you think that getting through all the flags you need for the Elemental Planes is a short path, you haven't done your research.<br>
<br>
Finally, for those saying &quot;Hey, this thread is moot because there is a quest for getting in&quot;, I say, then do the quest.  You will have worked hard to get in, and since you will be only one of a few who has access to the zone, you'll be on your best behavior since getting a res won't be a given. Please don't try and justify getting PoP progression flags when &quot;all you're after is xp flags&quot;.  There is a world of difference between the flag the quest gives you and the Aerin Dar flag.<br>
<br>
And again, for those claiming this is about xp zone &quot;protection&quot;, I don't xp in HoH.  6-12 soloing or duoing casters and the xp camps are full, and they rarely want a rogue who can't really contribute to their kiting/root doting/charm soloing.<br>
<br>
For those claiming this is about &quot;cash cow&quot; hoarding - there is no loot that drops in great quantity in HoH that sells for large quantities of cash.  Wristbands of strategy are barely better than BD bracers.  Windblades?  Gone.  Spectral drops?  Sure, those average about one to two in eight hours or more of xp grinding (or so my casters tell me, and it bears through when I used to xp there).  And of course, let's remember, not every spectral turned in suddenly yields a 50k+ spell, how many copies of Pacification or Greater Fetter do you have?  We get most of our spectrals off the PoP flag mobs we kill for progression.  (Those claiming these flag mobs have no loot, please take notice).  The zone mobs aren't what have the loot, its the flagging mobs - the ones we need to further our progression.<br>
<br>
I don't want my HoH trials blown by some xp group that sees a red named giving out what looks like a quest and blows my guilds plans for the night when I have finally worked out those who need flags and have managed to get them online.  <br>
<br>
I am tired of watching people kite in the GY claiming &quot;its an xp spot&quot; as they kill the guy who just got a res, who couldn't move his body if he wanted to.<br>
<br>
I am tired of having 10-15 straggler guildmates die when we go to do a trial because some idiot left a Recurso see invis mob from the Far Left Courtyard at the zone in (for those who have never been there, this would be akin to someone leaving a see invis Desert Giant in Plane of Storms at the zone in in terms of distance and work taken to accomplish, this is not lazy stupidity).  No, I have no desire to limit people's &quot;xp zones&quot;, if the HoH trials were somehow protected from every xp &quot;group&quot; in HoH like Aerin Dar is, I wouldn't care about you being in HoH xping.<br>
<br>
Do the guilds that got in on their own do kite in the GY or leave SIBs at the zone?  Sure, sometimes, but a heck of a lot more common these days than before.  And when it is one of those guilds, a simple tell gets the problem fixed.  And they never blow trials on us, just like we never blow them.  They know that if we have extra flags available, we will do the event and help them out with a few flags, and vice versa.  Blowing content is counter to their best interest.  A guild that teamed, and thus is not extended that same courtesy, could easily be a hindrance with an axe to grind.<br>
<br>
I will stop now, before I get more complaints about long posts. <p>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.noble-blade.net&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;http://www.noble-blade.net/images/ezboard/sig-small.gif&quot; align=&quot;left&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;Karadin Firethorne&lt;br&gt;Assassin of The Rathe&lt;br&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.noble-blade.net&quot;&gt;Noble Blade&lt;/a&gt; <br>
