<br>
That is why we are attmpting to create a NEW rule for these types of mobs.  A rule that many of us believe should parrell the no teaming rule that rotations us.<br>
<br>
To main reason people are drawing this parrell how these flags mobs advance a guild simialarly to how a rotation mob advances a guild.   All of the largesr guilds on the server have agreed to share the various content through the use of rotations, this sharing of content slows the progressing of guild greatly.  For example, BotS had to share the loot from Cursed during the last days of Luclin, when that loot would have made then a stronger guild (having better equiped members, more mana, more hps, etc).  <br>
<br>
PoP flag mobs are even more directly linked to progessing through the game.  Getting a new flag generally gives you access to a new zone, with new mobs to fight both exp mobs and boss mobs.  This in turn grants you better loot, and in the case of PoP possibly the most important loot of all, parchments.<br>
<br>
Now the problem we are facing is that on rotation mobs everyone has agreed that to be on a rotation, you have to kill the mob by yourself.  Whatever entity you are, you must do it alone.  To gain access to this content, you must be able to kill it alone.  <br>
<br>
Then we get to PoP flag mobs, which have not needed to be on any formal rotations to date for a few reasons.  And because of this fact that they are not on rotation, people are now teaming up to progress further into the game than they would be able to achieve alone.<br>
<br>
This is the main problem.  The larger guilds have agreed to slow down thier progression through the game by allowing anyone that can kill a mob to join its rotation, but now the smaller guilds are trying to speed up thier own progression through the game even further by teaming up to kill mobs they would not be able to do alone.  The larger guilds feel this is an abuse of the rotation system that restricts them to only one share of the content on rotation mobs, while smaller guilds that are teaming up in PoP get multiple turns.<br>
<br>
It would be like Tindi Losi breaking into 3 smaller guilds for all Rotation mobs, then those 3 guilds working together to advance through PoP.<br>
<br>
The problem never was CB and VoLS teaming up to kill a mob, it was the fact that they teamed up to progress further in the game in PoP, but remain seperate entities to progress through non PoP rotation mobs.<br>
<br>
This is why we are asking for a new disignation for PoP flag mobs, ones that advance a guild further into the game.  And new rules on these mobs that mirror the restrictions already in place on rotation mobs currently. <p><P><A HREF="http://www.jakefitch.com/asb/char_detail.asp?Name=Milambus" TARGET="_blank"><IMG SRC="http://jakefitch.com/sig/eq/sig1.jpg" HEIGHT="150" WIDTH="400" ALT="Milambus Mandragon" BORDER="0"></A></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm11.showMessageRange?topicID=297.topic&start=1&stop=20>1</a> <b>2</b>  </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm11.showPrevMessage?topicID=297.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm11.showNextMessage?topicID=297.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm11.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=297.topic&index=33><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/gfx/addReply1.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm11.emailToFriend?topicID=297.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm11.threadControl?topicID=297.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/deleteThreadFire.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm11.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=297.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm11.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=297.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </